column283: Possible choices of my experience with various devices include: "I had never heard of it" / "I had heard of it, but did not know much about it" / "I had heard of it and have been considering getting one", but no "I have heard of it, know enough about it, but have no need of it", which describes several, so I was forced to say that I don't know much about it even though I do. You're implying that the only reason people don't want [something] is because they don't know enough about it, which is clearly not necessarily true.
On the automatic light that turns on when someone approaches the house, I do have one but I have stopped using it because it came on when a car would drive by.
Everything worked fine. No problems here.
I found this study to be very interesting,liked doing it.
No comments, thank you and I hope your research goes well
